  "intent": "Set up a big PCR run across four 384-well plates. First, take samples from a regular 96-well plate and distribute them to specific spots on the four bigger plates - basically splitting each sample into multiple wells. Then grab some master mix from the thermocycler and add a tiny bit to each well where you put the samples. The robot handles all the precise positioning and timing to make sure everything gets distributed properly.",
